<div class="container" align="left">
<h3>ScrumBut!</h3>
<hr>
<h6>ScrumButs to avoid:</h6>
<p>ScrumButs is an initiative by the originators of scrum.<br>
  It is designed to assist people who think they get agile (but don't really), to GET IT!<br>
<ol>
  <li><img alt="red cross" class="img-fluid"  src="/images/redcross.png" >&nbsp;&nbsp;Goalless, soulless Scrum</li>
  <li><img alt="red cross" class="img-fluid"  src="/images/redcross.png" >&nbsp;&nbsp;Cherry-picking
    practices and premature process optimization </li>
  <li><img alt="red cross" class="img-fluid"  src="/images/redcross.png" >&nbsp;&nbsp;Marginalizing (<a href="/images/scrumvalues.jpg" target="_blank">no respect</a> / understanding for) the Scrum Master (<a href="/images/scrumgovernance.png" target="_blank">who's role is to be in charge of scrum method and scrum / agile process improvement</a>)</li>
  <li><img alt="red cross" class="img-fluid"  src="/images/redcross.png" >&nbsp;&nbsp;Shooting the Scrum messenger</li>
  <li><img alt="red cross" class="img-fluid"  src="/images/redcross.png" >&nbsp;&nbsp;Planning
    paralysis </li>
  <li><img alt="red cross" class="img-fluid"  src="/images/redcross.png" >&nbsp;&nbsp;Mis-aligned stories </li>
  <li><img alt="red cross" class="img-fluid"  src="/images/redcross.png" >&nbsp;&nbsp;Command and control-style micro management <br>
    (<a href="/images/scrumgovernance.png" target="_blank">PO (Business)</a> <a href="/images/scrumdevhorse.jpg" target="_blank">riding the Dev work horse hard</a>) <br>
    (Someone/s on (or, from outside the team, imposing on) team thinking command and control) </li>
  <li><img alt="red cross" class="img-fluid"  src="/images/redcross.png" >&nbsp;&nbsp;Overlaying unrealistic and not agreed delivery milestones (to meet unrealistic "heroic" business deadlines)<br>
    that violate agile (scrum) method; i.e. evolving to a solution sprint by sprint. </li>
  <li><img alt="red cross" class="img-fluid"  src="/images/redcross.png" >&nbsp;&nbsp;Individual heroics </li>
  <li><img alt="red cross" class="img-fluid"  src="/images/redcross.png" >&nbsp;&nbsp;Smoke and mirror demos <br>
    (no demo deck agreed up front and signed off by the PO after Sprint Review) </li>
  <li><img alt="red cross" class="img-fluid"  src="/images/redcross.png" >&nbsp;&nbsp;Lack of risk management </li>
  <li><img alt="red cross" class="img-fluid"  src="/images/redcross.png" >&nbsp;&nbsp;The
    vicious cycle of over commitment </li>
  <li><img alt="red cross" class="img-fluid"  src="/images/redcross.png" >&nbsp;&nbsp;Stalled improvement </li>
  <li><img alt="red cross" class="img-fluid"  src="/images/redcross.png" >&nbsp;&nbsp;An inability to regularly <a href="/release" target="_blank">release</a> <a href="/workingsoftware" target="_blank">working software</a> => UAT => PROD that is valuable to business </li>
  <li><img alt="red cross" class="img-fluid"  src="/images/redcross.png" >&nbsp;&nbsp;An inability (sprint by sprint) to <a href="/images/vmodelbevel.jpg" target="_blank">"Mind the Gap"</a> <br>
    (This could pertain to at lack of
    sufficient attention to detail with regard to the Capability Maturity processes <a href="/pmway/?slide=5" target="_blank">PP, PMC, REQM, CM, VER and VAL (and others)</a>, all above <a href="/pmway/?slide=4" target="_blank">CM L1</a>)</li>
  <li><img alt="red cross" class="img-fluid"  src="/images/redcross.png" >&nbsp;&nbsp;Lack of attention to software solution surviving in Technology Stack (insufficient resources or unstable network etc.) <br>
    (<a href="/pmway/?slide=6" target="_blank">I.e. per People, Process and Technology triad)</a><br>
    (<a href="/pmway/?slide=8" target="_blank">Answers, typically, are found in the careful application of ITIL processes</a> (<a href="/pmway/?slide=9" target="_blank">of which DevOps</a> is simply faster ITIL))</li>
</ol>
<br>
<br>
